WEBVTT

00:00:04.060 --> 00:00:06.420
Not being able to use your computer

00:00:06.420 --> 00:00:09.240
because your mouse doesn't work is frustrating.

00:00:09.240 --> 00:00:11.920
<v Audio Description>A man drops his computer mouse off the desk

00:00:11.920 --> 00:00:14.260
<v Audio Description>The computer mouse no longer works

00:00:14.260 --> 00:00:17.600
Many people use only the keyboard to navigate websites

00:00:17.600 --> 00:00:20.120
Either through preference or circumstance.

00:00:20.120 --> 00:00:23.620
<v Audio Description>A man with a wheelchair is using a mouth-stick to type

00:00:23.620 --> 00:00:26.100
Whether it's temporarily limited mobility

00:00:26.100 --> 00:00:29.520
<v Audio Description>A woman with her arm in a sling is typing on a keyboard

00:00:29.520 --> 00:00:32.960
<v Audio Description>but the website requires the use of a mouse to select the date.

00:00:32.960 --> 00:00:34.840
A permanent physical disability

00:00:34.840 --> 00:00:38.060
<v Audio Description>The man with the wheelchair also cannot use the site.

00:00:38.060 --> 00:00:40.060
or simply a broken mouse

00:00:40.060 --> 00:00:41.620
The result is the same

00:00:41.620 --> 00:00:44.740
Websites and apps need to be operable by keyboard

00:00:44.740 --> 00:00:48.360
<v Audio Description>He switches to a different website that allows typing the date.

00:00:48.360 --> 00:00:49.860
Web accessibility

00:00:49.860 --> 00:00:52.700
Essential for some, useful for all.
